dcterms:description: UCM multi-label dataset is reproduced by assigning all aerial images collected in UCM dataset with newly defined object labels. The dataset contains 2100 images with 17 candidate object labels including building, sand, dock, court, tree, sea, bare soil, mobile home, ship, field, tank, water, grass, pavement, chaparral, and car.
dcterms:title: UCM multi-label dataset

dcterms:description: AID multi-label dataset is produced by relabeling images in the AID dataset, which consists of 10000 high-resolution aerial images collected from worldwide Google Earth imagery. The dataset is more challenging due to diverse spatial resolutions of images, more scenes, and more samples.
dcterms:title: AID multi-label dataset
